Developers/Contributers should follow these rules:

Licence
-------
All code files must contain the GPL v2+ header
All contributors must update the copyright holders on edit

Exceptions: 
* interpolateBM: same license as scipy

Code structure
--------------

* All source code goes in the src folder under a subdirector of the subproject
* For experiments, use ini files. Add some defaults/example to the inifile folder
* For data needed for experiments/test, use the data folder.

For real data you do not want to commit, add the text rdata. gitignore contains the 
string *.rdat*, eg confidentialdata.rdat.conc